doc.after: Saskatchewan Saskatchewan and Alberta the twin provinces were both formed 1 Sept 1905 by an Act of the Dominion Parliament which gave them an identical constitution Saskatchewan derives its name from the important river Kissiskatchiwan or Swift Current now better known under the abbreviation of Saskatchewan whose two branches drain it from west to east
